location.name: Rattlesnake Lodge Trail (from Ox Creek Rd.)

mediaNotes: OVEN was on approx. 4 meters up on a dead, exposed branch on the edge of a clearing (dry, rocky outcropping thinly populated by mountain laurel).

There were three OVEN singing in this vicinity; in addition to the one I recorded, one approx. 50 meters behind me and another 50 meters to the left across a creek.  Additionally, I observed a fourth walking on the ground and low branches below the one I recorded.  The subject of this recording would fly from the ground up to a bare branch in a white pine approx 7 meters up; the three parts of this recording represent three trips to the ground.  Habitat is mainly white pine with very open understory.
